      "reasoning": "The filing states: 'On April 15, 2016, Dr. Hung received an unsolicited letter, dated April 13, 2016, from Dr. Brandicourt, setting forth a non-binding proposal from Sanofi to acquire Medivation for $52.50 per share.' The letter was dated April 13 (when Sanofi made the offer) but received April 15 (when Medivation learned of it). Alex used the letter date (April 13), which is the conventional choice for when the bidder made the proposal. The pipeline used the receipt date (April 15), which is the date the target became aware of it. Both are defensible readings of the filing text, though the letter-date convention is more standard in M&A bid coding."
