      "reasoning": "The pipeline derived a Sanofi 'drop' on August 10 via EXIT-03 (selected-to-advance observation omitted an otherwise active subject), citing span_0028 where the board authorized advancing Pfizer, Company 1, and Company 4 into a second round. However, Sanofi was NOT one of the five 'Interested Parties' (Pfizer + Companies 1-4, defined at lines 839-841 of the filing). Sanofi signed a confidentiality agreement on July 5 and received data room access July 7, but never submitted a preliminary proposal on August 8 alongside the Interested Parties. The span_0028 board decision on August 10 concerned which Interested Parties to advance -- it did not directly address Sanofi. Alex dated the drop at August 20 (the final bid deadline day), but the filing provides no explicit statement of when Sanofi ceased participation. The pipeline's inference is structurally flawed because it attributes a board decision about the Interested Parties to Sanofi, who was on a separate track. Neither date is cleanly grounded in filing text for Sanofi specifically."
